JOHANNESBURG - ANC MP Boy Mamabolo has refused to apologise for accusing EFF leader Julius Malema of spousal abuse in parliament. Malema's wife Mantwa has filed a defamation suit against Mamabolo but he's undeterred, saying he will not retract any statements.Mantwa Malema demanded the parliamentary representative issue a public apology for claiming that Malema abused her and admit that he lied. She says claims the EFF leader abused her, are untrue and it amounts to emotional abuse of herself and her children, whom she says are being mocked at school. Julius Malema is also threatening to sue the ANC MP for R1-million if he does not retract his allegation. Mamabolo says he'll see them in court.